What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Coil Coating Market?

Market Analysis and Insights

Coil Coating Market

The coil coating market is expected to gain market growth in the forecast period of 2022 to 2029. Data Bridge Market Research analyses the market to reach at an estimated value of USD 4.2 billion by 2029 and to grow at a CAGR of 5.4% in the above-mentioned forecast period.

Coil coatings are basically a liquid paint system that generally comprises back coat, topcoat and primers. They are available in a wide range of colors and finishes that can be applied to steel /aluminium coils with the help of rolls. These can be cured in a minute's time and recoiled for delivery to end users. This coating procedure generally includes cleaning of the substrate, drying, application of primer coating and top coating, and the foil lamination.

The factors such as high demand from downstream industries, rising penetration in aerospace applications and pharmaceutical packaging along with rising development in the automotive, construction and appliance industry are the root cause fueling up the market growth rate. The factors expected to cushion the growth of the coil coating market in the forecast period are the rise in the demand for functional coil coatings from electrical and electronic, construction, and automotive industries and so forth, rise in the increase in the disposable income of customers and the enhancement in the standard of living. Additionally, the strict government regulations, rising environmental compliance, growing competitiveness of leading coil coating manufacturers, high demand from downstream industries and high demand from industrial sectors owing to its high tensile strength, eco-friendly nature and good adhesion property along with product quality and differentiation will further carve the way for the growth of market. The growing production and adoption of coil coatings is expected to cushion the growth of the market within the above mentioned forecast period. On the other hand, the high energy and electricity consumption required for coil coating process and pricey coating technologies is expected to impede the growth of the coil coating market. The lack of proper and safe transportation facilities is also expected to hamper the overall growth of the market.

The constant innovation and developments along with growing demand for residential and commercial furniture which is estimated to generate numerous opportunities for the market. On the flip side, increasing demand for lightweight materials in automotive industry and STORAGE and transportation difficulty of coil coating pose as a major challenge to the growth of the coil coating market.

